The teaching takes the form of physical exercises in group work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The overall objective of the subject is the physical form of the student and facilitating self-reflection in ability, acquiring the right relaxation and safety techniques, developing a sense of rhythm, coordination and body memory, providing basic knowledge of the construction and functioning of human mobility aparatus and skills to sense and use your body as a systemic whole.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course: - is able to assess the physical form of his or her body and to avoid injury and overload; - is able to see and evaluate individual bodily movements; - have evolved individually from their sense of rhythm, coordination and body memory - is able to control his posture and movement.
